table-0804-185.caption: Grounded in Greece
data: "The Muddy White Rose" (泥まみれの白バラ)

In spite of the premonition of José's accident with a carriage, Nadja is hard at work customizing an umbrella in a bid to improvise a new dance during the convergent course toward Mikonos; once on the island, Nadja spots a young man that she thinks is Francis that prompts her to leap from the Happy Carrier Car in a bid to give chase and resolve the confusing »Granada deja vu«. Observing a rendezvous with a woman Nadja recognizes from Granada confirms quod erat demonstrandum that it is Francis she is seeing and prompts Nadja to stealthily bide her time -- a volition successful until an untimely gust of wind literally blows her cover along with her hat. Even with Francis explaining Mary-Anne Hamilton being his childhood friend along with Keith being his elder twin brother, Nadja's understandable confusion about her love life soon takes a back seat to a pair of boys angry about Francis inadvertently having purchased homeless destitution for them with what he intended to be a benevolent donation; having seen a ruined structure, some hefty introspection becomes the road ahead -- a journey that George objects as he grounds Nadja from performing that day for having zoned out. The lesson ultimately at play here is that all of the good intentions in the world does nothing to counterbalance the reality of it being possible to cause unintentional collateral damage; while Nadja prosecutes a dance sequence only to find it of no utility even though falling in love with the Harcourt brothers is not a crime, Francis struggles to reconstruct a building in a bid to redeem himself for his failure in heeding the principle of »caveat emptor« in regards to the venal ex-headmaster of the Pegasus Orphanage.

table-0804-186.caption: Excavation Egypt
data: "The End of the Nile -- The Secret of the Ring" (ナイルの果て・指輪の秘密)

Nadja's ecstasy at discovering a diary entry indicating Egypt a significant part of her mother's prologue along with it being the Dandelion Troupe's next destination soon gives way to Rosemary having the epiphany that she will find neither the prince nor the »happily ever after« she wants if she remains on the Gonzales-ke payrolls; upon realizing that Nadja is an aristocrat and recognizing the juicy opportunity for what it is, Rosemary volunteers to accompany Rosso and Bianco. Upon arriving in Egypt, Abel explains Nadja that Collette met an archeologist named Professor Edward Harrison prior to dancing a waltz with him at a party that will certainly recount the experience with immense euphoria -- id est, if he can be found; having depleted stamina and various kinds of structural contention as the salary for the safari of visiting so many excavation sites both foreign and domestic, Nadja decides to continue searching for the Professor on her own recalling that it has been Christian's dream to visit Egypt. How all this ultimately plays out is that the late Professor Harrison was Christian's mentor who taught him some insight about the ring in Nadja's brooch along with how it came into the possession of Preminger-ke -- a member of which is Nadja's mother Collette; the Austrian city of Vienna firmly decided upon as the next destination once Kennosuke is rescued from being lost in a below-round crypt, the Dandelion Troupe performs an entertainment exhibition for all the excavators gathered that night.

"The Brooch that Vanished Into the Pyramid" (ピラミッドに消えたブローチ)

Nadja learning of her genetic link with Preminger-ke along with it being part of the reason that the archeological excavation team of which Christian is a member thanks to the tutelage of the late Professor Edward Harrison is not an insignificant milestone along with Vienna being the place to go; however, attaining significant milestones is a game that two can play -- a potent lesson that Nadja is forced to learn the hard way when Rosso and Bianco ambush her as she is riding a camel through town during a stopover to resupply the Happy Carrier Car. Even if she does manage to break away from the two goons and make her way to a pyramid as per the advice of a feline wishing to repay her earlier intercession with a shopkeeper, Nadja is in such a panic that Rosso and Bianco soon catch up with her to seize the brooch from her; however, as was the case the first attempt at Applefield Orphanage, the only hitch is Bianco's carelessness denying the two goons an escape route with Nadja's brooch!!! Drawing upon the data she has about the Egyptian pyramids, Nadja is ultimately forced by the circumstances to declare an armistice with Rosso and Bianco as she assumes a leadership role in navigating through the pyramid upon figuring out that the two goons are just as much cowards as they are clumsy clods; however, the particular configuration of Nadja's cerebral software places her at a very eerie parity with Rosso and Bianco who leave her tied up in the desert prior to riding off with her brooch.

table-0804-188.caption: Enlightenment Bouken -- Salzburg
data: "Danger Lurks! The Black Rose's Life on the Line" (危うし！命を賭けた黒バラ)

The euphoria of Nadja's diurnal side trip in Rome oblivious to her genetic filial connection to Collette Preminger is definitely not insignificant considering how her reaction to Rosso and Bianco cornering her in Egypt really threw the Troupe off balance; still, even after having covered the lengthy distance between Rome and Salzburg, it is necessary to turn east toward Vienna with some kind of action plan -- a volition made quite difficult by an irreversibly damaged gear in the Happy Carrier Car's drive train requiring a week-long layover. The Dandelion Troupe advertising itself -- a policeman interfering Kennosuke and Nadja's efforts thereof -- soon takes a back seat to the Black Rose's pending arrival; upon completing their home commute, Nadja and Kennosuke have it explained that the Troupe has been invited to a charity concert hosted by the mayor three days later and paid in advance. Unable to shut her mind down, Nadja's decision to take a nocturnal stroll sets the stage for her to get caught up in the Black Rose trying to evade the police; in a bid to cool off Nadja's umbrage at the playboy humiliation of being behaved toward as his girlfriend and Keith's derision of Francis as a hypocrite buying redemptive relevance, Keith explains Nadja his observations of aristocratic social customs -- one of which cost his mother her life and is none too pleased to learn that Nadja had her brooch stolen. Seeing that Nadja will not heed his admonition of distance from Preminger-ke, Keith decides to raid Herman's mansion but soon has demonstrated that he has ultimately bitten off more than can be safely chewed even if he does successfully stalemate Rosso and Bianco interfering him; while Herman lashes out with a series of rapid-fire whip blasts in a bid to scare Keith into confessing his motives, Nadja decides that the Troupe should do what it does best in order to earn the necessary funds to repair the Car and set course toward Vienna in spite of it being a trap ...

table-0804-177.caption: Authentication Confrontation -- Vienna
data: "Rosemary -- the Scheme Behind the Smile" (ローズマリー笑顔の陰謀)

Nadja's ecstasy at having arrived in Vienna hoping to meet her mother Collette is mirrored by Duke Preminger's displeasure at an internal family matter being brought above-ground against his wishes; while Herman laughs all the way to the bank prior to explaining Rosemary the syllabus of what is to happen next, the Dandelion Troupe's astonishment of Harvey's journalism being perverted to Herman's advantage is making it clear that nullifying the utility of Nadja's recently regained brooch is all part of Rosemary's dramatic pauper-to-princess volition. The Troupe is of one mind that Rosemary needs to have an absolute curtain call happen to her; thanks to Granny Anna's social research, a party that night at Viscount Strohein's mansion is the opportunity to do just that. A smuggling operation as a stevedore and a waltz dance sequence give way to a break in the action for Nadja to ultimately drag Rosemary into what is in many ways the conversation that would have taken place in Granada if the circumstances at Gonzales-ke were more cooperative; while Herman bootstraps himself to the reality that there is such a person as Nadja Preminger who knows that he exists and that he seeks the Preminger duchy for his own reasons, Nadja recovers herself from being kicked out just in time for the feature presentation of the night: Rosemary having doubled down on the whole pot and gone for broke against resuming the life of a pauper in rags -- not unlike Collette's dress which she defenestrates right in front of Nadja along with her trunk and hat!!!

table-0804-179.caption: Subterfuge Investigation London @ England
data: "Alone at Home" (ひとりぼっちの故郷)

An empty belly, finding that finances dictate the train trip to Cherbourg be conducted in two stages, having her food stolen by a mischievous child, having it twice demonstrated that good Samaritan intercessions can be quite costly, and having to twice employ some creative panhandling that could have gotten her arrested on the spot ... one would think that Nadja would be warmly greeted upon her return to Applefield Orphanage -- something just below that which Rosemary is experiencing as Collette presents her with a variety of pastries she baked; while Rosemary repulses Herman's subordination attempts unaware of Duke Preminger's very narrow definition of »useful« that excludes even his own biological children, Nadja is astonished to find that the only welcome she gets is Applefield Orphanage as a tomb-like shell of itself as a result of Headmistress Applefield's death. Even if Herman did not directly bring it about as part of his plans for the Preminger-ke fortune, the fact still remains that Nadja is at a crossroads where she will have to ultimately chart a new course for gathering witnesses on her behalf; thanks to Raphel's circuitous musical counsel tabulating the data that she has already acquired during her journey as the two lodge for the night in Headmistress Applefield's former office, Nadja recalls some details from when she received Collette's suitcase that herald a new vector to prosecute -- straight to London!!!

"The Lullaby the Piano is Connected To" (ピアノがつなぐ子守歌)

Nadja realizing that searching London for the person who sent her Collette's ball gown and diary in spite of the fact that Applefield Orphanage has been abandoned soon after its headmistress's death is not an insignificant volte-face if the colorful journey to Cherbourg is anything to go by; still, searching for the requisite post office is far more easily contemplated than actually conducted particularly when Nadja demonstrates herself oblivious to several crucial urban mechanics -- the greatest of which is there being very few major cities that do not have a multi-branch urban postal system. Nadja wandering upon the National Museum where she hopes to locate Christian only for the efforts thereof to come for naught becomes the genesis for a trip down memory lane that overlooks that Nadja would have learned that Edna Grey is house-sitting for Christian after having sent the suitcase she now carries had she not been so quick to depart; upon having it explained that Harvey is not available, Nadja starts to feel despondent at the chasm separating her from Collette until she sees an advertisement for a John Whittard piano recital. Not much time has to pass before enough plausible evidence accumulates for the piano concert to have ultimately reflected John being well aware of Nadja's solo journey to England in search of data about her prologue to dethrone Rosemary as a cheap emulation; backstage after the concert, John presents the sheet music of Nadja's favorite lullaby complete with the signature of her father Raymond Colville as he guides her to Raymond's former music teacher who is only too happy to share plenty of data about the late French composer complete with a photograph.

"Who Do I Like? Ultimate Decision!" (どっちが好き？究極の選択！)

Learning that her late father Raymond Colville was a gentle family man and that it was he who composed the lullaby she now knows ... progress of that scope is worthy of a celebration not unlike the party to which John brings Nadja ... id est, once a long standing issue has been resolved as evidenced by Nadja's astonishment upon encountering Francis; as if he heard his brother's declaration of contacting Preminger-ke to properly explain things, Keith has arrived to escort Nadja to Waltmüller-ke where Collette resides with her husband Albert instead of to the Duke. As was previously demonstrated at every encounter with Kennosuke and TJ, Nadja is dismayed at Keith and Francis's adversarial divergent concourse degenerating into a scuffle of which she is not only rudely enjoined neutrality but also presented with a dangerous opportunity: choosing both the route to Vienna and to what her heart wants; further inflaming matters, the Harcourt twins are not the only ones paying close attention to Nadja's decision. The family politics of both Hamilton-ke and Harcourt-ke set aside for the moment, Mary-Anne's possessiveness towards Francis has not a few parallels to Carmén who was in love with the José of the past after she married for money; Nadja now dried off, Julietta recounts her story about Antonio Fabiani along with how his courting attempts became tamer as her fiancé Leonardo began paying attention to her as a woman. José and Carmén having broken up because of their unrealistic expectations ... in a bid to avert that conclusion, Nadja ultimately has to compare Keith's valorous initiative toward getting his hands dirty on her behalf versus Francis's stratospheric sophistication having helped her sort through some confusing issues; if Mary-Anne's jealousy is anything to go by, it will take a lot more than a collaborative waltz and a trip to Vienna with Francis to reverse Rosemary's theatrics and give Nadja the choice of how to proceed after meeting her mother Collette.

Mikaze tries to convince Bunmei in a Cult ceremony that Maya is actually the Key of Nostradamus and asks his help to separate Maya from her spellbook, but he ends up warning Maya about Mikaze's intentions instead. Maya fakes her own death with Chihiro's help to dissuade the enemy, but Bunmei leads Mikaze to them. Mikaze is revealed to be a Black Mage and she takes the spellbook and burns it. She immobilizes Bunmei with a spell, while, with Chihiro's help, Maya and the others escape with Mikaze behind their back. Chihiro tries to get Maya away from the village, but their plans are thwarted by Mikaze's brainwashed cultists. Mikaze confronts them and Chihiro has no other choice than to battle her. Chihiro is revealed to be a White Mage.

"A thousand wind, the search for beauty" "Sen no Kaze, Bi no Tomeyuki" (千の風、美の尋めゆき)

Chihiro battles Mikaze to protect Maya but she ends up being defeated by Mikaze.It is revealed that Mikaze was behind all the strange incidents in the village, having summoned the Mothmen and the Chupacabras With her last ounce of strength, she frees Bunmei from the spell he was put in. Maya is helped by Chihiro's assistant in the form of a flying jaguar. Mikaze manages to get a direct hit and Maya and her guardian plummets and crash at the roof of the Occult Academy. Bunmei reaches Maya in time and reveals that the true spellbook wasn't destroyed, but was only a decoy to fool Mikaze. Mikaze is shocked and tries to kill Bunmei with her Black Magic. Maya snaps a picture of them fighting only to realize that it was the Key of Nostradamus. Bunmei resists her spell and reads aloud the chant to seal all beings of darkness from the area. Maya repeats after him and Mikaze disappears in a brilliant flash of light along with all the other monster and anomalies of the village. The town returns to normal and Maya and Bunmei, having thought that they destroyed the Nostradamus' Key, enjoy once again peace.

Mikaze is defeated, but Bunmei finds that the future is still unaltered. Maya invited Fumiaki, Bunmei's younger self to the year-end ceremonies. Bunmei contacts the future and is told that meeting his younger self might be the True Nostradamus Key. Maya cancels the opening, evoking Fumiaki's mother's rage. Fumiaki wanders off alone to Occult Academy, while his mother searches frantically for him. Before Bunmei's departure, Bunmei encounters his younger self and a rift in the fabric of time occurs.Fumiaki tries to fight the aliens, but is quickly cast aside. Bunmei grabs the spoon his mother placed in Fumiaki's pocket and regains his Psychokinetic Abilities. He fights the aliens on his own and enters the rift to close it, but not before telling Maya to take care of his younger self. The Rift disappears and Maya and Fumiaki walk off into the distance. In the future, Maya's father, who was revealed to be still alive and commander of the Alien Resistance, finds that the world has changed. "Night of the Phantom Thief »Black Rose«" (怪盗黒バラの夜)

Between nearly being barbecued and almost being abducted by a pair of clumsy goons driven by family politics that she knows nothing about, Nadja's mind is a real mess -- and this is to say nothing of how Nadja will handle suddenly finding herself in the midst of the Dandelion Troupe!!! Racing away from the perplexed Troupe which is trying to decide how to handle its new stewardship, Nadja finds the anguishing aftermath of last night's fire and quickly realizes that the remaining undamaged portion of the Orphanage is a down payment of her continued presence in spite of Rosso and Bianco asking around about her; unfortunately, Nadja soon finds that her individual capability to exercise her two most viable options at this point -- establishing her own micro-economy and finding her mother -- is of very acute finity. Further inflaming matters is that the Dandelion Troupe has visited unto Nadja much stricter admission requirements -- the dexterous performance of an improvised dance routine; Nadja doing her thing on stage after an impromptu customization job obfuscates the vortex of why Rosso and Bianco are after Nadja: Herman Preminger wishes to take the choice away from his father about who is to be the heir of the duchy. A nocturnal stroll upon arriving in London to help shut her mind down before Rita's twin lions Crème and Chocolat decide to give chase after a mouse becomes the ultimate backdrop for Nadja's first encounter with the phantom thief Black Rose; after evading some police officers, Black Rose imparts some sage but abrasive counsel about nocturnal travel as a parting gift -- much to Nadja's offended displeasure.

data: The Powells are an average ordinary family that is falling apart due to Jim's inability to bond with his wife, Stephanie whose career as a research professional is flourishing as well as his kids, Daphne and J.J. as they succumb to their teenage problems. However, superpower changes occur after a plane crash during a family trip in Brazil which grants Jim super strength and invulnerability which he uses to stop crime in the city with the help of his friend and defense attorney, George. Stephanie is able to move extremely fast and shares this secret with her assistant, Katie while the two work on a newly approved research on a mysterious plant. Daphne has problems dealing with her telepathy when she is distracted by everyone's thoughts. J.J, who is initially perceived as unaffected develops a super-brain which allows him to deduce and learn things instantly.

However, superpower changes occur after a plane crash during a family trip in Brazil which grants Jim super strength and invulnerability which he uses to stop crime in the city with the help of his friend and defense attorney, George. Stephanie is able to move extremely fast and shares this secret with her assistant, Katie while the two work on a newly approved research on a mysterious plant. Daphne has problems dealing with her telepathy when she is distracted by everyone's thoughts. JJ is accused of cheating, but won't tell his family about his power. Stephanie finds a sample of the Amazon water and discovers it is just regular water, wondering how she and the family got the superpowers. Jim stops a bank robbery, but Det. Yvonne Cho sees him running from the scene and later confronts him, and Jim tells her about his powers. Yvonne tells him that if he shows up at another crime scene he will be arrested. Daphne learns to control her powers by focusing on her thoughts only. Finally, a criminal with superpowers arrives in Yvonne's apartment, shooting her with her own gun via telekinesis.

Jim feels guilty when he unintentionally causes harm to a civilian during one of his crime fighting operations and to further complicate matters, starts suspecting Daphne's boyfriend Chris when a vial of super-serum vanishes from the house. Stephanie develops an antidote for Joshua but soon discovers the truth about him from none other than Dr. King. Katie is thrilled when Joshua proposes to her but his dark past rises again to destroy their relationship. J.J. is blackmailed by Mr. Litchfield to join the academic decathlon team in exchange for the provision of a merit scholarship to Natalie, unaware of the fact that Litchfield is secretly working for Dr. King.

data: "Confrontation of the two Nadjas" (二人のナージャ、対決！)

Arriving in Vienna without the police giving chase is not an insignificant accomplishment as Francis catalyzes Nadja's disembarkation from the train galvanized by excitement at getting to finally meet her mother Collette; what Nadja and Francis do not realize is that Rosemary is equally prepared to keep her ill-gotten »principality« as the Preminger-ke successor and that Duke Preminger seeks to forestall a scandal that injures the prestige of his family. Even if one ignores Nadja barging into Duke Preminger's office thinking that she will meet Collette, it soon becomes quite clear that Rosemary holds all the cards and is prepared for all of Nadja's attempts to prove her identity -- the brooch, the diary, the ball gown, the lullaby, the circumstances at Applefield Orphanage prior to its fiery destruction ... nothing that Nadja says or does is able to convince the Duke; worst of all, Herman remembers what Keith looks like and comes up with the idea to have the police arrest Francis!!! Even with Nadja and Francis unjustly incarcerated as per his plan, Herman ultimately finds that Rosemary is neither ignorant nor welcoming of his money-driven hypocrisy; while Rosemary laughs all the way to the bank at Duke Preminger declaring her his heiress confident at nobody being able to successfully stalemate her, one does have to wonder if Keith's proposal for Nadja to visit Waltmüller-ke in search of Collette would been the wiser choice.

"Silence! The Captured White Rose" (沈黙！囚われの白バラ)

Francis's capture for Keith's actions as the Black Rose along with Nadja as a result of Rosemary's lies is quite a distasteful and disheartening turn of events when it appears in the newspaper if Harvey and Collette's astonishment is anything to go by; while Nadja divides her energies between despondency at the circumstances and refusing to capitulate, Mary-Anne comes to grips with Francis's motives and is none too pleased at how Nadja's infatuation has caused the whole situation. What neither Nadja nor Mary-Anne realizes is that Francis has composed a roundabout strategy to get Nadja introduced into the media without taking the choice away from Keith about whether to come above-ground; while Collette and Albert setting course for the police station to visit Nadja is a natural reaction, that volition is also quite predictable and easily nullified. Nadja's understandable umbrage at her rough landing and her renewed resolve to exonerate Francis obfuscates that Rosemary's »clemency« has the ultimate silver lining of Collette finally wising up to the stormy Preminger-ke politics; while Harvey and Nadja compute their endgame strategy to crush Herman's plans, Keith and Francis finally work out their differences upon hearing Nadja's lullaby -- not realizing that Rosemary subconsciously wishes to implode Herman's plans just as much as they do.

Nadja's understandable umbrage at her rough landing and her renewed resolve to exonerate Francis obfuscates that Rosemary's »clemency« has the ultimate silver lining of Collette finally wising up to the stormy Preminger-ke politics; while Harvey and Nadja compute their endgame strategy to crush Herman's plans, Keith and Francis finally work out their differences upon hearing Nadja's lullaby -- not realizing that Rosemary subconsciously wishes to implode Herman's plans just as much as they do.
"Reversal! The End of the Black Rose" (逆転！黒バラの最後)

Considering that keeping out of their reach has been a necessary evil in order for her to meet Collette, there is a not-at-all insignificant or sweet irony that Nadja is now searching for Rosso and Bianco even though their clumsiness forced her out of the Applefield Orphanage and that convincing the two goons to betray Herman could at best be quite costly; after all, Herman did purchase their services away from Duke Preminger -- not an inexpensive thing to do. Mulling over the rumors of the Black Rose in Vienna during a recess for lunch, Harvey realizes that this data could cause Nadja to do something reckless when he spots Keith signaling him to a secluded destination; while he and Keith do a bit of male bonding over how they both strive for a more just society, Harvey makes the mistake of leaving Nadja unattended long enough for her to wander near the Colorado-ke mansion where she briefly spots Bianco and decides to further investigate -- a big mistake since what she saw is a snapshot of Herman under immense contention as it becomes apparent that his master plan has failed. Oscar has found that Collette's counsel has borne fruit in the form of a way to coerce departure of Herman whose creditor Antonio Fabiani accompanies him -- complete repayment of the debt upon Herman's permanent departure from Colorado-ke; as has been previously demonstrated the case with desperate cornered villains, Herman arrogantly balks at this gracious exit offer to instead prosecute a series of desperate -- and ill-fated -- maneuvers to save face. Even before the Black Rose delivers Vienna his farewell address to Harvey's delight, there is ultimately no denying that the endgame is in full swing and affords only three choices: lead, follow, or get out of the way; still, it remains to be seen if Rosso and Bianco finally seeing the light about Herman has come about in time ...

Even with the data of Duke Preminger's obsession with what he feels are the best interests of the Duchy as a parting gift from Rosemary, it takes a moment for Nadja to recover herself into voting with her feet against not being allowed to meet Collette -- something that has already happened -- only to find that »Absolutely not!!!« is the last thing the Duke wants to hear; what the Duke fails to realize is that being trapped in Herman's dungeon is the zenith of the experience Nadja has attained during her search for Collette and that his kind of family government has not worked so well if Herman is anything to go by. Collette is not slow in rushing over the Preminger-ke to fetch Nadja or in confronting the butler escorting her for his role in the mother-daughter separation as Nadja is effecting her high-altitude escape; a joyous reunion later, Collette takes Nadja to Waltmüller-ke where the two at long last spend some time as mother and daughter. As if having sensed Duke Preminger's computations about how to make her his successor under Collette's nose, Keith and Francis pay Nadja a nocturnal visit to prosecute a conversation about the future that seems weighted toward Nadja ultimately staying with Preminger-ke; as has been previously demonstrated from multiple sources, becoming a blue-blood is the last thing on Nadja's mind as she reads Duke Preminger the riot act for his misdeeds and answers the question of what to do after meeting Collette: seeing the entire world as a dancer for the Dandelion Troupe -- which has arrived to spirit her away.

table-0804-446.caption: Main courses
data: The Swedish name literally means "blood pudding". Sweetened and spiced, it is eaten with lingonberry jam, and sometimes bacon.
Other than pig blood, the ingredients include flour, pork, raisins and spices.
A classical Swedish dish consting of pork with stewed brown beans.
Casserole based on chicken with bananas, peanuts and bacon. "Invented" in the 1970s.
Salmon cured with salt and sugar with herbs.

Sausage, from Småland, made of coarsely ground pork, barley and potatoes. It is prepared by first fermenting it and then lightly smoking it. This method of cooking creates a distinct, both acidic and slightly smoky flavor. It's traditionally eaten with dill-stewed potatoes and pickled beetroot.
Meat stewed with onion, vegetables and spices.
Mix of chopped and fried meat, onions, pre-boiled potatoes, often prepared from left-overs. Other ingredients are often added as well, such as sausages, bacon or even salmon (instead of the meat).
mashed rutabaga, potatoes, carrots served with long-boiled salted pork loin.
Like a very big multi-layer sandwich. Comes with many different fillings and toppings.

Fileted fresh herring, two filets put flesh to flesh, skin out, with dill, salt and ground white pepper between and breadcrumbs on the outside, and then fried in butter until golden. Eaten with mashed potatoes and lingonberry jam. Very different from surströmming.
Being fermented, Surströmming has a strong odor and unique flavour and is considered an acquired taste even among swedes.
Patty of ground veal, cream, eggs and coated in breadcrumbs.

table-0804-373.caption: Order of miners and rescuers
data: Recorded video footage to be sent up to families on the surface. He had helped to get his brother Renan a job in the mine.
An electrical specialist known as "the presenter" because he acted as a spokesman and guide on videos that the miners made. He ended one video with "Over to you in the studio."
A former Chilean Army corporal who served in the Beagle Conflict, a border dispute with neighboring Argentina.
The only Bolivian among the 33, a heavy machinery operator who moved to Chile a decade ago.
Given the responsibility of checking air quality and the youngest man trapped. He had only been a miner for five months and had just had a baby daughter.
In a video message he told his wife and baby daughter Britany: "I will fight to the end to be with you."

Penned the famous note "Estamos bien en el refugio, los 33" (English: "We are well in the shelter, the 33"), which was discovered attached to a probe 17 days after the mine collapse. He is a grandfather who suffers from kidney problems and has been on medication for diabetes.
A drill operator. His longtime partner Cristina Núñez accepted his marriage proposal while he was underground.
The eldest of the trapped miners, he had been thinking of retiring that November. (Note: *Multiple reliable sources have reported his age as between 60 and 65.)
Suffers from kidney problems and hypertension. Had worked in the mine for nine years.
A part-time miner who also drives a taxi and likes horse racing. He was said to be unhappy with interference from psychologists.
A mechanic who only went into the mine on the day of the collapse to fix a vehicle. He was also in the February 2010 Chile earthquake.
An electrician and father of four who told his family: "This hell is killing me. When I sleep I dream we are in an oven."
Truck driver, was given the role of medical assistant in the mine.
Told his longtime partner Jessica Yáñez that he would marry her in a church as soon as he got out.
He had worked in the mine for less than six months when the accident happened. His brother Esteban was trapped with him.

A drill operator, he is the son of a miner, and his father was once trapped for a week underground. His sister María led prayers at Camp Hope, the makeshift settlement that sprang up at the mine's entrance.
Served as the group medic and supervised their medical care.
A father-of-three who had worked in the mine for five months.
Friends with fellow trapped miner Pedro Cortez.
A preacher who has worked in mining for 33 years, he had become the miners' pastor and organized daily prayers.
Trapped along with his older brother Florencio.
Had his birthday in the mine on 9 September.
A well known former football player known as the "magic mortar".
A mechanic who had worked in the mine for two years.
A hydraulics engineer who was in the February 2010 Chile earthquake. He moved north, finding work at the mine to support his wife and two children.
Went to school near the mine. He and his friend Carlos Bugueno, who was also trapped, started work there at the same time.
The group's communications specialist. His wife gave birth to a daughter on Sept 14 and he watched the arrival on video. He named his daughter Esperanza, which means "Hope".

"Full of Danger! A Date in Rome" (危険がいっぱい！ローマのデート)

As has been demonstrated at the previous engagement, Christian has a near-complete computation crash upon seeing Nadja doing her thing as a dancer even if the collaborative flag dance with Kennosuke is relatively vanilla compared to the first dance routine which involves an abrupt costume change; while Kennosuke jealously fumes in silence, Nadja is astonished and delighted at Christian being chosen as a member of a university research team bound for Egypt. As if having heard Christian point out the interdependence between Rome and Egypt in ancient times, George pipes up to suggest that Nadja accompany Christian on a guided tour of the Roman ruins; a sequence of daydreaming on the part of both Granny Anna and Christian later, Nadja is enjoying herself as Christian leads her through his itinerary complete with a historical prologue about the Egyptian queen Cleopatra and her two Roman paramours. The only flaw with this date is a fleeing pickpocket knocking aside Nadja -- and her brooch being securely fastened to her dress; while interdicting the thief is easily accomplished, retrieving the brooch turns out to be quite an urban scavenger hunt!!! The keystone that ultimately implodes this whole circus is a boy named Lucca wanting to gift the brooch to his infirm grandmother but is a bit of a butterfingers which works to Nadja's advantage; when all the excitement settles down aside from Nadja and Kennosuke's collaborative flag show, Christian is demonstrated a caring gentleman on course to realize his dreams while Lucca attains his wish for his grandmother to go outside and spend time with him.

"Mother and Daughter Who Keep Passing Each Other -- The Two Birthdays" (すれ違う母娘・ふたつの誕生日)

The cool-down period after a performance becomes the forum of a divergent concourse about Granny Anna's exact age along with how to acknowledge her birthday; while she computes as to what present to purchase, Nadja does not realize that her biological mother Collette is in the immediate vicinity with her father and her new husband Count Albert Waltmüller. Collette's destination is a hotel where her nephew Oscar Colorado is anguished about an edict from his stepfather Herman about a debutante ball; as has been demonstrated with Nadja who is using her diary as a road map, Collette is of the perspective that Oscar should attend the ball since it is how she met her first husband -- a French pianist named Raymond. Even though she led Raymond through an ill-fated bid to vote with her feet from Preminger-ke because of Duke Preminger's »money > love« matrimonial emphasis, Collette soon finds that the poverty endemic to being a working-class young family in Paris is not an insignificant disadvantage -- especially after Raymond dies in a train accident; as if having sensed that she has reached her limits as a young single mother, Duke Preminger orders Collette brought back to Vienna -- Edna's execution of these orders involving Nadja's »death« to become an Applefield orphan. Either because of her grief or some kind of maternal telepathy, Collette senses Nadja's efforts toward searching for her and predicts that they will ultimately bear fruit once the circumstances start to cooperate; even though Bianco and Rosso wasting their energy searching for Nadja in Milan demonstrates them quite slow on the uptake, Duke Preminger makes it clear that he expects Nadja to have a certain configuration of cerebral software to become his heiress.

"Help me! The Memory of Fire" (助けて！炎の記憶)

Rita leading her lions Crème and Chocolat through a routine exhibition soon becomes anything but when an inebriated customer pipes up with a »fire = felicity« perspective that hits really close to home; unfortunately, George's intercession of throwing the astonished inebriate into a nearby fountain comes too late as the damage is already done. The adult Troupe members dealing with bad hangovers from the previous night forces Nadja to compensate and redress the aftermath -- the clumsiness thereof at its most obvious when Nadja obliviously charges Rita vigilance of the fire; fortunately, Kennosuke picks up on Rita being under immense contention but not the cause until Rita flees with Nadja's brooch. Granny Anna and George recall a circus troupe that was forced to disband because of immense fatalities -- two of which were Rita's parents; galvanized by how Rita along with Crème and Chocolat escaped with their lives at an immense cost, the other Troupe members decide to diverge and discover not realizing that Rita is too frightened to read their anxiety for what it really is. A careless stable-hand and an errant mouse along with easily panicked horses are not slow in ultimately setting in motion what no amount of emphatic apologies can accomplish -- an immense inferno that really illuminates the good intentions of the Dandelion Troupe; galvanized by Kennosuke racing to her rescue and frightened of Nadja being barbecued along with Chocolat, Rita locates an egress and -- with an effort -- recoups her ability to speak!!!

table-0804-528.caption: References
data: Question: Develop the question that critically defines the broad nature of the spatial and temporal patterns the analyst is seeking to ultimately identify.
Evaluate conclusion: Generate re-evaluations of current conclusions requiring the marshaling of additional evidence to support or disconfirm the analysis.
Grounding and Team Building: Build a potential repertoire of prototypical geospatial and temporal patterns from which a number of hypothetical patterns are selected, and form the analytic team.
Deconstruct the synthesis: Reexamine the table of hypothesis and evidence beginning with the rankings
Hypothesis development: Select all the reasonably possible geospatial and temporal patterns that might match the pattern envisioned during the development of the question.
Examine the evidence: Re-examination of collected evidence or search for new evidence that may suggest new geospatial or temporal patterns.
Evidence Development: Extract snippets from items discovered in grounding; develop the evidence by applying schemas so that it can be used more easily to draw conclusions.
Re-evaluate the hypotheses: New hypotheses may generate new searches, further data extraction, or a search for additional raw data.
Fusion: Compare the evidence to each hypothetical geospatial and temporal pattern to determine consistency.
Question your own grounding in the problem: New hypotheses may cause analysts to broaden their grounding in prototypical geospatial and temporal patterns.
Conclusions: Propose which hypothetical pattern(s) is (are) most consistent with the evidence and answer the question.
Question the question: Revalidate with the client the nature of the geospatial and temporal patterns the analyst is ultimately seeking to identify.

table-0804-184.caption: Arc V:  Revelation Spain
data: "Great Terror! The Ghost Ship of the Mediterranean" (恐怖！地中海の幽霊船)

The majestic clarity of the Mediterranean Sea and the increasing proximity to the Spanish city of Barcelona make for plenty to converse; while Rita is in her childish seventh heaven with the marine fauna; Nadja is not happy about Granny Anna charging her the solo synthesis of a flamenco costume. Kennosuke teasing George about not being able to hunt for treasure at sea prompts one of the crewmen to enjoin silence of the male Troupe members prior to explaining them the story of Spain transporting back treasure from South America which prompted British and French pirates to try their hand -- the greatest of which is the Castanets whose career was extinguished in a battle with the Spanish armada; in a bid to get revenge, the Castanets attack any and all vessels they come across. Not much time has to pass before it becomes apparent that the crew is playing a prank on the Troupe -- part of which Sylvie points out; the perfect proximity now perpetuated, the pirates board the ship only to find that the Dandelion Troupe intent upon stalemating them with just as much zeal. The skeleton key that ultimately elucidates this whole circus involves Sylvie's leadership along with inebriation overcoming Thomas's aversion to violence frightening the pirates; a powerful uppercut from a sober and none-too-pleased George later, the Dandelion Troupe celebrates its victory and Nadja's successful completion of her flamenco dance costume.

"Olé! The Solar Matador and Flamenco!" (オーレ！太陽の闘牛士とフラメンコ)

The ability to unilaterally synthesize a flamenco dance costume in the midst of a pirate attack en route to Spain is not an insignificant asset; still, Nadja soon finds that there is not much in her database to help her deal with a belligerent bull -- or the dexterity with which a matador named José Rodriguez interjects some temperance into the ill-tempered bovine prior to resuming his work commute. José's destination is a bullfighting arena in which Abel explains Nadja the fortitude with which the yin-and-yang homeostasis practiced by Spanish men along with a syllabus of Spanish bullfights -- a lesson that Nadja encounters the hard way when Granny Anna charges her the acquisition of Anselma's instructive assistance in building her flamenco dancing prowess; while Nadja fuels herself with paella and gets a good night's sleep, she does not realize that José has much bigger fish to fry than receiving her gratitude for his intercession. It ultimately becomes clear that Anselma has been reading Nadja's cerebral software as the young teenager prosecutes one flamenco dance attempt after another; upon seeing Nadja's attempt at deep introspection, José explains Nadja his professional prologue and imparts some counsel to be honest with herself about her motives.

It ultimately becomes clear that Anselma has been reading Nadja's cerebral software as the young teenager prosecutes one flamenco dance attempt after another; upon seeing Nadja's attempt at deep introspection, José explains Nadja his professional prologue and imparts some counsel to be honest with herself about her motives.

"The Return of the Beautiful Betrayer" (帰ってきた裏切りの美女)
"The other side of Francis" (フランシスの向こう側)

The Dandelion Troupe's arrival in Granada is quite the geography lesson for Nadja as she has demonstrated the utility of the siesta when she finds that Abel is the only one still awake; galvanized by Abel's counsel to stay in the shade to avoid the diurnal heat scored at fifty Celsius degrees while reading a newspaper article about the phantom thief Black Rose having arrived in Granada, Nadja soon has demonstrated that the only kind of thief that should demand her immediate attention is a pair of pickpockets that laugh at her admiring the scenery by making off with her brooch. Much to Nadja's relief, the pickpockets do not get very far thanks to the dexterous interdiction of a young nobleman that reminds Nadja to never part with the brooch although the hostile operatives employed by Preminger-ke are more of a threat than common street hoodlums; the subsequent euphoric diurnal engagement during which Nadja generally behaves as would a child half her chronological age makes it clear that the aristocratic equestrian that interceded for Nadja at the Applefield Orphanage was not Francis but his elder twin brother Keith Harcourt -- and that Nadja is in love with them both!!! The night-and-day dichotomy between Francis and Keith ultimately becomes even more confusing when Keith demonstrates himself as quite a gentleman in his own way as he assures Nadja that the feelings she is experiencing are absolutely genuine and not at all misplaced; still, seeing Francis with a lady that in every way appears to be his girlfriend and also Keith put on the same mask that the Black Rose wears is definitely a challenge for Nadja's cerebral software to process!!!

table-0804-182.caption: Arc III:  Expedition Switzerland
data: "Francis in The Morning Light" (朝陽の中のフランシス)

The euphoria of Nadja completing her first self-made dance costume under Granny Anna's tutelage takes a back seat to the beauty of the Swiss countryside as the Happy Carrier Car converges on its next destination -- Le Man Orphanage -- which once allowed the Dandelion Troupe an emergency nocturnal layover; in commemoration of this hospitality, the Troupe prosecutes a charity show when it is in the area. This time around, Nadja performs her Tyrolean dance as the opening act which soon garners audience participation; after the remaining Troupe members do their thing, it soon becomes apparent that the important dance is resolving her feelings toward Francis who has arrived to appraise the epilogue of a recently built library. Upon her frantic search coming up bumpkus oblivious to the fact that Francis is in the same boat, Nadja recalls a bit of her childhood prologue when she sees a tree outside in the yard and ascends it; a timely breeze later, Francis's retrieval of Nadja's hat sets the stage to explain Nadja a bit of his childhood prologue where he was taught the idea of »noblesse oblige« as something that anyone can do to make another person happy. If the previous day is any indication, Nadja ultimately answers the »noblesse oblige« question by guiding all the orphans through her Tyrolean dance; unable to shut her mind down, Nadja ventures out for a stroll where she ascends the tree and is pleasantly surprised to find Francis following suit with quite a memorable parting gift!!!

"A Lie at the Alpine Flower Festival" (アルプス花祭りのウソ)

Having one's infatuation reciprocated complete with a daybreak first kiss is not an insignificant event as Nadja dreamily demonstrates before George summons the other Troupe members to witness their next destination -- a village preparing to host a festival; as the Happy Carrier Car converges upon the village, a boyish looking child pauses his efforts in recovering his sled for another downhill glide. Much to George's surprise, Nadja has a much better answer to the question of how the Dandelion Troupe can introduce itself when she recognizes the Tyrolean dance and swiftly joins in to give a free sample of the Troupe's services; once camp is set up, Kennosuke admonishes proximity of Crème and Chocolat only to soon find himself facing a tomboy whose cerebral software is a very close match for that of TJ Livingston. Not much time has to pass before the tomboyish Zabine demonstrates herself as a viable alternate universe reply to what a true friendship between TJ and Kennosuke would look like; while Rita dries off from her soggy displeasure at being left behind, the ensuing concourse begs the question about where the threshold is of whether deception is benign or even constructive versus being destructive. The Alpine Flower Festival the next day where the Dandelion Troupe does its thing ultimately makes it clear that Zabine being female has nothing to do with the fact that she holds Kennosuke near and dear to her heart for the correct reasons; as an ancillary honorarium, Zabine makes quite an impact when she takes the stage wearing a festival dress after Nadja repairs the result of Rita playing with her cosmetics.

table-0804-181.caption: Arc II:  Scavenger Hunt France
data: "The Diary of the Ball that Ties Mother and Daughter" (母子を結ぶ舞踏会の日記)

Nadja has met several milestones in England after leaving the Applefield Orphanage along with some hair-raising experiences have forced her to really discern what it is that is important to her; while she is processing all this data through writing her own diary account, George proudly bellowing out visual acquisition of the Eiffel Tower drives it home to Nadja that she is no longer in her native England. Fortunately for the other Dandelion Troupe members, George cannot override the necessity of bolstering the coffers; this time around, Nadja's dancing draws the attention of a boy named TJ Livingston who has promptly developed an infatuation for her that raises the question of Kennosuke's feelings for Nadja. TJ and Kennosuke are not slow in taking an intense aversion to each other much to Nadja's dismay; galvanized by her umbrage at the testosterone tempest brewing in her midst and having neutrality rudely enjoined of her, Nadja decides for throwing a »Stop this at once!!!« bucket full of water on the two boys. Upon recalling Paris mentioned in the diary, Nadja devises the perfect vehicle for TJ and Kennosuke to cooperate with each other; upon Abel easily interpreting the German exposition, Nadja commissions the two boys that she be accompanied during her search for a painter named Alphonse Jean Maley mentioned in the diary. A near-flawless record of being repulsed into the street and generally snubbed quickly demonstrates the null utility of searching for the quarry painter at the art stores; while the three kids compute their next move, a little girl named Madeleine wanders in seeking navigational assistance to her mother. The amended search sequence becomes the preamble of TJ and Kennosuke to prosecute an adversarial divergent concourse over how to best help Madeleine that ultimately delves into the boys' prologues who understand that they each have half of the solution complete with a heart of gold; as an ancillary unexpected bonus, Nadja kills two birds with one stone by successfully reuniting Madeleine with her mother and stumbling across Alphonse Jean Maley whose sparse data about his prologue with Nadja's mother gives Nadja encouragement to keep up the search complete with a pencil sketch.

"The Masquerade Ball's Trap" (仮面舞踏会のワナ)

As the Black Rose introduces himself to France with a raid to retrieve a painting from the white-collar criminal Lubich, the Dandelion Troupe is on recess in a plaza forming a general consensus of approval while Nadja pauses from her letter-writing to fume about the Black Rose's abrasive appraisal of her corporeal dimensions at her previous engagement complete with a very caustic and pragmatic perspective of all thieves being the same; little does Nadja realize that there are thieves that can successfully steal intangible items when Rita wanders into the path of an automobile whose chauffeur is only able to avoid the mute child by sideswiping a lamppost!!! Further inflaming matters, the car's aristocratic passengers Simone Monterlant and her nephew Fernando Gonzales read Nadja's emphatic entreaties for clemency as an excellent opportunity for revenge; wielding Nadja's umbrage at the insult about her morals and meager dimensions to her advantage, Simone charges Nadja an exhibition of her dance at the upcoming nocturnal masquerade party. As if to lend credence to Granny Anna's remark about life lessons being learned the hard way, not much time has to pass before Nadja soon has it demonstrated that Monterlant-ke is a viper's nest when Fernando grabs and drags her away with such celerity that she drops all of her equipment in the process. Disgusted at Simone and Fernando's ultimate emphasis on vindictive humiliation, a party-goer named Leonardo Cardinale and his dressmaker friend Thierry Rothschild combine forces to customize Nadja into an aristocratic young lady using a sample ballroom dress before Leonardo's girlfriend Lady Therese steps in and takes over; somehow having reasoned that she has been knocked on her caboose to learn the same lesson that he wants to teach the fuming and hysterical Simone, the real Black Rose sweeps Nadja into a very insightful waltz that illustrates his virtue and his personal perspective of the world.

"Broken Wing and Tears of Love" (折れた翼と恋の涙)

As if to commend her on learning the importance of greater discretion with her umbrage, Nadja sees Rita noisily greeting a traveling minstrel named Raphael that apparently has an extensive prologue with the Dandelion Troupe; upon seeing Raphael entertain the other Troupe members by composing song lyrics on the fly, Sylvie is forced to relive the anguishing final moments of her former paramour Antonio Fabiani prior to her first encounter with Raphael. Galvanized at the prospect of an escape hatch that she can wield to Nadja's detriment, Sylvie is not slow or shy about stalemating Nadja's inquiries about her love life before insisting upon resuming the home commute during a sustenance supply run; reading Sylvie's lack of negation as an affirmation, Nadja approaches Raphael about a song of good luck only to have the point driven home that there are not a few people in the world that have complicated love lives that are best kept out of the community concourse. Seeing that there is nobody that has not had to ultimately bite the bullet, Sylvie further reinforces this lesson by explaining Nadja the data she has about Raphael's prologue along with coming to grips with the fact that exerting an effort toward a satisfactory epilogue is a difficult necessity; while Raphael is of the perspective that his journey is not complete, he does gift Nadja a collaborative concert with Sylvie as a reward for configuring all the back-end logistics of his reunion.

"The Troubled Genius Pianist!" (悩める天才ピアニスト！)

Having had demonstrated that love can both create and resolve its own complexities, Nadja tries to interpret all this data through writing in her diary when Granny Anna exhorts her assistance in transporting some payload; the destination this time around is the residence of Mireille Moreau who has commissioned the synthesis of several hats. Not a lot of time has to pass before Mireille demonstrates Nadja that there is more than meets the eye when the tweenage dancer is shown a salon where a pianist named John Whittard is playing a tune on the piano before pausing to make some notes on the musical score in front of him -- until Leonardo and Thierry greet Nadja so noisily that John takes umbrage and is rather abrasive with his reproof prior to his hasty departure in a huff which sets the stage for Nadja to have explained an insightful bit of John's prologue. During the home commute with the bread meant to accompany lunch, Kennosuke gets a little homesick as he signals an interest in having some rice -- a sentiment with which Nadja sympathizes -- before Rita cries out at the sight of John about to jump into the river; while not exactly grateful for the intervention, John gets a crash course in civilized behavior when Créme and Chocolat abruptly inhibit his departure. The stubborn young music composer ultimately finds that the price of this intercession includes the powerful lesson that the entire Dandelion Troupe can give as good as it gets since it has had plenty of practice during its travels; to help gift-wrap the lesson, Nadja chases down John for a spot of tea over which prologues are exchanged -- a significant portion of which involves Francis offering John some tea not unlike what Nadja just did!!!

"The Music Box with Memories of Two" (ふたつの想い出オルゴール)

Galvanized with jubilation at the above-aggregate revenue from a performance, George declares tomorrow as a rest day -- a decree that is music to Harvey and TJ's ears as they pipe up about a flea market being hosted the next day; as has been demonstrated to be the case, Kennosuke and TJ's rivalry flares up much to Nadja's frustration. Nadja-tachi's (Nadja with Kennosuke, Rita, TJ, and Harvey in convoy) visit to the Clignancourt flea market starts off with a vendor trying to capitalize on George's affinity for treasure-hunting before having the signs of the vendor's treachery pointed out to him; while the outraged George gives the swindler a sword-point lesson in »caveat venditor«, a chance encounter with Fernando Gonzales is the forum by which Kennosuke and TJ rally their combined hatred as they enjoin the haughty aristocrat to find an item that garners the most bang for the buck. As can be predicted from what has been demonstrated about the configuration of his cerebral software, Fernando's emphasis on purchasing an old clock of great sentimental value to the shopkeeper Gérard instigates such umbrage that Nadja ultimately decides to answer this question with an obdurate slap across Fernando's chops complete with a harangue about how there are valuable things that simply cannot be bought with any sum of money; in gratitude for Kennosuke having successfully repaired the clock, Gérard gifts Nadja a tangible clue to her mother -- a music box that her mother had sold to him a decade before.

"A Narrow Escape!! A Confession of Love in Paris" (危機一髪！パリの告白)

Having the previous day off has borne great fruit for Nadja as she has learned that she did spend some time with her mother as a baby and that the music box she now has been given plays a significant role in that prologue; what Nadja does not realize is that another element of her prologue is about to pay her a visit -- Oliver with a big crush on her that he has been wanting to confess for quite some time. Rosso and Bianco do not have the problem of what to do upon seeing Nadja as is demonstrated when they are not slow in giving chase when Oliver accompanies her on an errand; while Oliver is quick-minded enough to lead Nadja in taking shelter in his workplace, this only convinces Rosso and Bianco to bide their time outside even though Oliver's boss promptly ejects them. The skeleton key that ultimately resolves what looks like Rosso and Bianco successfully completing their mission comes in the form of Harvey imparting a whack of insight to the locomotives of the two goons when TJ's jealousy of Oliver inadvertently corners the three kids; crushed that Nadja's cerebral software does not allow for him or TJ to be seen as a possible paramour, Oliver settles for Nadja's affirmation of the two as siblings as George gathers up the Dandelion Troupe and sets course eastward.

table-0804-187.caption: Fiscal Stopover -- Rome @ Italy
data: "Farewell, Dandelion Troupe" (さよならダンデライオン一座)
"The Wind's Trick -- the Irony of Fate" (風のいたずら・運命の皮肉)

As if to congratulate the Dandelion Troupe for working out its internal problems in a timely manner, the day's performance is anything but routine when Nadja's mother Collette Preminger requests a layover of the coachman to watch Nadja prosecute a flamenco dance which Johanna objects; further sweetening the deal, the daily revenue has bolstered the Troupe's war chest to where a single show the next day is all it will take to set out toward Vienna once Granny Anna purchases some additional supplies. As has been demonstrated the case, the wind blowing away Nadja's hat and Nadja's chase thereof becomes the preamble for Nadja's first face-to-face encounter with Collette who is hiding from Johanna searching for her; once the threat passes, it soon becomes apparent that there is a negligibly minute discrepancy spread between Nadja and Collette's cerebral software -- almost like the two are the same person. Collette explains Nadja her desire to locate a caldarroste vendor whose wares Collette had once eaten with her late husband Raymond when they were in Rome; commiserating Collette's caged songbird home life and sensing a connection with Collette, Nadja decides for catalyzing this volition in spite of the fact that she only has until dusk. The sought-after roasted chestnuts now in digestion along with Nadja leading Collette through ascending a tree for the first time and recovering herself from Collette falling on her do very little to counterbalance the fact that Nadja's quest would have ultimately come to a close if Johanna and Oscar had only been a few seconds later in arriving so that Nadja could tell Collette her name; furthermore, it also would not have taken the whole day for Collette to recognize Nadja as her daughter if not for Rosso and Bianco's ambush in Egypt.

table-0804-579.caption: Season 2 (2006)
data: Near-death experiences are discussed with two individuals who claim to have been to the other side. Two people who have been to the other side tell of the supernatural experiences surrounding their own deaths. As a young girl, Katherine encounters a brilliant white light accompanied by a voice as she lies dying on an operating table. Twelve years old at the time, something within the white light gave her the opportunity to choose life or to choose death. She chose life, and then chose to use that life for good, as part of Angels Anonymous. Don has spent his life terrified of water. He was finally able to figure out why when he visited a strange town and discovered he was the reincarnation of a boy who had drowned the day he was born.

"My Dad's Ghost Saved My Mom's Life"

Purported messages from long-dead fathers and their impact on their living former spouses are discussed. Barbara's father had loved morse code and numerology, and one night she heard strange systematic tapping, and figured it was him sending her a message, but couldn't figure out what the message was. Then her mom, living in Montreal, had a heart attack. The doctors said it wasn't serious, and not to bother traveling, but Barbara knew the tapping was telling her to go. She dropped everything and went. By the time she got there, her mom was almost dead, but then suddenly she had a miraculous recovery. Elsie lost her dad six years ago, and grieved heavily. On the anniversary of his death, she was looking at a picture of him on a table, when it moved toward her. Because of this, she's learned to listen to the spirits. So, when Elsie woke suddenly one night and felt compelled to tell her healthy mom to see a doctor right away, she phoned immediately. The next morning her mom went, where they discovered a blood clot that would have killed her within 24 hours had she not gone.

data: DI Jack Armstrong and his new partner, bright fast-tracker DI Georgina Dixon come together at a car showroom where top salesman Karl Mercer is found dead in the boot of a car. The suspects are all employees of the car dealership from sales staff to mechanics and Georgina is exasperated by Jacks casual attitude and he is annoyed by her determination to solve their first case together.

The mismatched detectives investigate the murder in a university library of student Laura Edwards who is studying gender studies. Jack goes undercover as a mature student to aid their investigation of the tutors and students and the complicated world of gender politics. In their private lives Georgina meets her perfect man and Jack obsesses over his girlfriend, Danielle, to the amusement of Georgina with his descriptions of their relationship.

When the headmaster of a hugely popular local primary school is murdered by a knitting needle in the neck Jack and Georgine quickly arrest one of the last five mothers to see him that morning. Realising they may have made a mistake further investigation reveals the headmaster was taking bribes from the mothers wanting their children accepted by his school. The school secretary is poisoned and Jack mesmerised by one of the mothers does not realise he too has been poisoned. Georgina's father announces he is divorcing her mother.

The thieves knew the combination, an inside job, so all the family and staff are suspects. Jack is distracted by an invitation to be best man at his brother's wedding, an invitation with a sting in the tail from a brother he despises. Georgina has problems when she experiments with online dating and is overwhelmed by the response.
